trend_summary: Across the series, moderate suburban fabric gradually fills vacant parcels, pushing housing into eastern and southern edges while commercial strips thicken along the north-south main road. Tree cover declines at expansion fronts but interior parks and golf course persist. Overall built-up footprint grows moderately without high-rise concentration, keeping a medium-density, predominantly suburban character.
notable_changes: Residential subdivisions extend east and southeast, replacing former woodland.
Commercial blocks and parking lots enlarge along the central arterial corridor.
New cul-de-sac streets appear within previously open parcels, indicating infill housing.
Southern shoreline shows reclamation or mudflat exposure, altering coastal land cover.
Tree canopy thins near new roads, although park and golf course greenery remains intact.
